# GIUSEPPE TERRAGNI
**Giuseppe Terragni** (April 18, 1904 â€“ July 19, 1943) was an Italian architect who worked primarily under the fascist regime of Benito Mussolini and pioneered the Italian modern movement under the rubric of Rationalism.
His most famous work is the Casa del Fascio built in Como, northern Italy, which was begun in 1932 and completed in 1936; it was built in accordance with the International Style of architecture and frescoed by abstract artist Mario Radice. In 1938, at the behest of Mussolini's fascist government, Terragni designed the Danteum, a monument to the Italian poet Dante Alighieri structured around the formal divisions of his greatest work, the Divine Comedy. 

![Giuseppe Terragni](http://spazioweb.inwind.it/alessandroarchi/Giuseppe_Terragni.jpg)

For this final project I've draw some Terragni's operas like:

* The Novocomum Table
* The Chair for Sant'Elia nursery school
* A Library prototype

___

## The Novocomum Table

Coffee table in burr oak characterized by three tops. The Novocomum Table was part of the furniture designed by the Italian designer for the headquarters of the Federation of Farmers, building Novocomum.
The cost of this table is about 2.000 Euro.

This is the REAL table:

![Real Novocomum Table](http://i39.tinypic.com/14bl56s.jpg)

And this is the table shape that I've draw:

![Shape of Novocomum Table](http://i41.tinypic.com/30dl7di.png)

For this shape I've decided to produce it with a final function that draw all the model, inside this function there are some basilar component (cuboid and closed cylinders) created using the parameters gived to the function.

To realize this shape I've used this functions:

1. Circle
2. Cylinder (edited for obtain close cylinders)
3. Cuboid
4. Color
5. T
6. R
7. S
8. Novocomum (writed for parameterize the shape)

The Novocomum function has as parameters the radius and the height of the table, then it produce a shape of the table.

This is the code of the edited version of the cylinder function:


    function CYLINDER(r,h){
    var domain1 = DOMAIN([[0,2*PI], [0,r]])([36,1]);
    var mapping = function(v){
    var a = v[0];
    var r = v[1];
    return [r*COS(a), r*SIN(a)];
    };
    var base = MAP(mapping)(domain1);
    var domain2 = DOMAIN([[-2*PI,2*PI]])([70]);
    var crc = circle(r);
    var model = MAP(crc)(domain2);
    var cil = EXTRUDE([h])(model);
    var cylinder = STRUCT([base,cil,T([2])([h])(base)]);
    return cylinder;
    };


Link to the source code: [Novocomum Table](https://github.com/cvdlab-cg/420076/blob/master/final-project/javascript/novocomum.js)

