## The Chair for Sant'Elia nursery school

The Sant'Elia nursery furniture is the last Sant'Elia challenging for Terragni.
This chair was used to furnish this nursery school

This is the REAL chair:

![REAL Sant'Elia nursery school chair](http://www.ilquintuplo.it/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/3627_ciac_foligno_terragni_04_sedia.jpg)

And this is the chair shape that I've draw:

![Shape of Sant'Elia nursery school chair](http://i39.tinypic.com/2pob9co.png)

For this model I've decided to draw all the model proceeding step-by-step starting from the top and ending to the bottom of the chair. The majority of the chair's support is realized using Bezier's curves.

To realize this shape I've used this functions:

1. Circle
2. Cylinder (edited for obtain close cylinders)
3. Cuboid
4. Color
5. T
6. R
7. S
8. Bezier
9. Intervals
10. Rotational_surface

The most difficult part of this chair shape, was to draw all the support for the chair. I've realized the back support for the backrest using Rotational_surface:

    //BACK SUPPORT

    var p1 = [[2,0,2],[1.98,0,1.85],[1.78,0,1.85],[1.8,0,2]]
    var c1 = BEZIER(S0)(p1)
    var mapp1 = ROTATIONAL_SURFACE(c1)
    var s1 = MAP(mapp1)(rot_domain)
    
    
    var p2 = [[2,0,2],[1.98,0,2.15],[1.78,0,2.15],[1.8,0,2]]
    var c2 = BEZIER(S0)(p2)
    var mapp2 = ROTATIONAL_SURFACE(c2)
    var s2 = MAP(mapp2)(rot_domain)

The rest of the chair's support was realized using Bezier, because it's not possible to draw the support by turning it on a specific angle but it's necessary to draw it point-to-point with Bezier curves like this:

    //ARMRESTS
    
    var p3 = [[2,-1,2],[1.98,-1,1.85],[1.78,-1,1.85],[1.8,-1,2]]
    var c3 = BEZIER(S0)(p3)
    
    var p4 = [[2,-1,2],[1.98,-1,2.15],[1.78,-1,2.15],[1.8,-1,2]]
    var c4 = BEZIER(S0)(p4)
    
    var s13 = BEZIER(S1)([c1,c3])
    var surf13 = MAP(s13)(Dom2D)
    
    var s24 = BEZIER(S1)([c2,c4])
    var surf24 = MAP(s24)(Dom2D)
    
    var sx_armrest = STRUCT([surf13,surf24])
    var dx_arst = R([0,1])([PI])(sx_armrest)
    var dx_armrest = T([1])([-1])(dx_arst)

    //FRONT TOP JUNCTIONS

    var p5 = [[2,-1.15,2],[2,-1,1.8],[1.8,-1,1.8],[1.8,-1.15,2]]
    var c5 = BEZIER(S0)(p5)
    
    var p6 = [[2,-1.15,2],[2,-1.3,2.1],[1.8,-1.3,2.1],[1.8,-1.15,2]]
    var c6 = BEZIER(S0)(p6)
    
    var p7 = [[2.02,-1.15,1.8],[2,-1,1.8],[1.8,-1,1.8],[1.78,-1.15,1.8]]
    var c7 = BEZIER(S0)(p7)
    
    var p8 = [[2.02,-1.15,1.8],[2,-1.3,1.8],[1.8,-1.3,1.8],[1.78,-1.15,1.8]]
    var c8 = BEZIER(S0)(p8)
    
    var s37 = BEZIER(S1)([c3,c5,c7])
    var surf37 = MAP(s37)(Dom2D)
    
    var s48 = BEZIER(S1)([c4,c6,c8])
    var surf48 = MAP(s48)(Dom2D)


Link to the source code: [The Chair for Sant'Elia nursery school](https://github.com/cvdlab-cg/420076/blob/master/final-project/javascript/sedia%20per%20asilo%20sant'elia.js)


