## A Library prototype
This prototype was drawing by Terragni, but never physically realized.
This was the last Terragni's project before his death.

This is the REAL library:

![REAL library prototype](http://lightstorage.ecodibergamo.it/media/2009/09/89732_1081199_PROTOTIPO__8774885_medium.jpg)

And this is the library shape that I've draw:

![Shape of Sant'Elia nursery school chair](http://i41.tinypic.com/rjktxe.png)

For this shape, I've decided to draw it using some functions created by me (Book_Spaces and Lateral_Shelfs) for drawing the majority of the model.
The library legs are realized using Bezier's curves.

To realize this shape I've used this functions:

1. Cuboid
2. Color
3. T
4. R
5. Bezier
6. Intervals
7. Rotational_surface
8. Book_Spaces (created for draw the spaces for the books)
9. Lateral_Shelfs (created for draw the lateral shelfs)

For this shape, I've created two new functions called:

* Book_Spaces 

        //Function that draw the library's book spaces
    
        function BOOK_SPACES(panel,n){
	    var shelf_h1 = T([0,1])([2,-1])(CUBOID([5.1,0.1,1.5]))
	    var level_1 = STRUCT([shelf_h1,panel])
	    for (var i = k ; i >= 0; i--) {
		    level_1 = STRUCT([level_1,T([0])([i])(panel)])
	    };
	    return level_1
        }
    
* and Lateral_Shelfs.    

    

        //Function that draw the library's lateral shelfs 

        function LATERAL_SHELFS(shelf_h0,n){
	    var closing = T([1])([-0.75])(CUBOID([0.1,0.75,1.5]))
	    var level_2 = STRUCT([shelf_h0,closing])
	    for (var g = k-2 ; g >= 0; g--) {
		    level_2 = STRUCT([level_2,T([1])([g*(-0.75)])    (STRUCT([shelf_h0,closing]))])
	    };
	    return level_2
        }


